eligious authority. Scott situates this controversy within the context of postmodern Thailand and the Asian economic crisis when reevaluations of wealth, global capitalism, and "Asian values" occupied a preeminent place in Thai public discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theravada. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842788140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438427881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438427881/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles